# Maze Code Finder

## Solution 1: Brute Force Approach

### Intuition

* The most direct idea is to take each word and try to build it from every cell in the grid.
* Whenever the current letter matches, we continue searching in the four allowed directions while making sure the same cell is not used twice in one path.
* This works because it checks every valid starting point and every valid path for each word.
* The downside is that many similar paths get explored again and again for different words, so this becomes expensive when the list of words is large.

### Approach

* Go through each word one by one.
* For each word, try to start the search from every cell that matches its first letter.
* Use depth first search to move up, down, left, and right while marking cells as used in the current path.
* If all letters of the current word are matched, add that word to the answer list.
* After each recursive search, unmark the current cell so it can be used in other paths.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```plaintext
dfs(r, c, idx, board, vis, word) {
    /* If all letters are already matched, this path is valid */
    if idx >= length of word {

        /* Successful path found */
        return true
    }

    /* Store the board dimensions for boundary checks */
    n = size of board
    m = size of board[0]

    /* Reject invalid positions, reused cells, or mismatched letters */
    if r < 0 || c < 0 || r >= n || c >= m || vis[r][c] || board[r][c] != word[idx] {

        /* This path cannot form the word */
        return false
    }

    /* Mark the current cell so it is not reused in this path */
    vis[r][c] = true

    /* Try moving upward to match the next letter */
    top = dfs(r - 1, c, idx + 1, board, vis, word)

    /* Try moving left to match the next letter */
    left = dfs(r, c - 1, idx + 1, board, vis, word)

    /* Try moving right to match the next letter */
    right = dfs(r, c + 1, idx + 1, board, vis, word)

    /* Try moving downward to match the next letter */
    down = dfs(r + 1, c, idx + 1, board, vis, word)

    /* Backtrack so this cell can be used in other search paths */
    vis[r][c] = false

    /* Return whether any direction completed the word */
    return top OR left OR right OR down
}

searchSecretCodes(board, words) {
    /* Create the answer list for all matched words */
    list = empty list

    /* Store the board dimensions once */
    n = size of board
    m = size of board[0]

    /* Track which cells are used in the current DFS path */
    vis = 2D boolean array of size n x m initialized to false

    /* Check every word independently */
    for each word in words {

        /* Track whether the current word has already been found */
        found = false

        /* Try every cell as a starting position */
        for i = 0 to n - 1 while found == false {

            /* Scan all columns in the current row */
            for j = 0 to m - 1 while found == false {

                /* Start DFS only when the first letter matches */
                if board[i][j] == word[0] {

                    /* Search for the complete word from this cell */
                    if dfs(i, j, 0, board, vis, word) == true {

                        /* Store the matched word once */
                        add word to list

                        /* Stop searching further for this word */
                        found = true
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }

    if(list is empty){
        return {"[]"}
    }
    /* Return all words that were found in the board */
    return list
}
