### Complexity Analysis

* **Time Complexity: `O(W * N * M * 4^L)`**

  * For each of the `W` words, we may try starting the search from every cell in the `N * M` board.
  * From each starting point, the recursive search can explore up to `4^L` paths in the worst case, where `L` is the word length.
  * The dominant term is `O(W * N * M * 4^L)` because each word is searched independently without sharing work across common prefixes.

* **Space Complexity: `O(N * M + L)`**

  * The visited matrix uses `O(N * M)` space, and the recursion stack can grow up to `O(L)` during one search path.
  * The remaining variables use only constant extra space beyond the answer list.
  * Total space used is `O(N * M + L)`.

## Solution 2: Optimal Approach

### Intuition

* Searching every word separately repeats a lot of work, especially when many words start with the same few letters.
* A trie groups all words by their shared prefixes, so one grid search can explore many words at the same time.
* While moving through the grid, we only continue along paths that still match some prefix in the trie, which cuts off useless searches early.
* This is much faster in practice because invalid paths are pruned as soon as they stop matching any word prefix.

### Approach

* Insert all words into a trie so shared starting parts are stored together.
* Start a board search only from cells whose letter appears at the top level of the trie.
* During the search, move in four directions only when the next cell continues a valid trie path.
* Whenever a trie node stores a complete word, add it to the answer and clear it there to avoid duplicates.
* Mark a board cell as used during the current path and restore it after backtracking.
* Remove empty trie branches after finishing a path so later searches become smaller.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```plaintext
class Node {
    /* Each node stores the next possible letters */
    children = empty map

    /* Store a completed word at the terminal node */
    word = ""
}

backtrack(row, col, parent, board) {
    /* Read the current board letter */
    letter = board[row][col]

    /* Move from the parent node to the matching trie node */
    currNode = parent.children[letter]

    /* If this trie node completes a word, record it once */
    if currNode.word is not empty {

        /* Save the found word in the answer list */
        add currNode.word to result

        /* Clear it to prevent duplicate insertion */
        currNode.word = ""
    }

    /* Mark the current board cell as used */
    board[row][col] = '#'

    /* Prepare the four possible movement directions */
    dirs = { {-1, 0}, {0, 1}, {1, 0}, {0, -1} }

    /* Explore all valid neighboring cells */
    for each dir in dirs {

        /* Compute the next board position */
        newRow = row + dir[0]
        newCol = col + dir[1]

        /* Continue only if the neighbor is inside the board and matches a trie edge */
        if newRow >= 0 && newRow < size of board && newCol >= 0 && newCol < size of board[0] && currNode.children contains board[newRow][newCol] {

            /* Recurse deeper along this matching prefix */
            backtrack(newRow, newCol, currNode, board)
        }
    }

    /* Restore the original letter after exploring all paths */
    board[row][col] = letter

    /* Remove the trie edge if no words remain below it */
    if currNode.children is empty {

        /* Prune this finished branch from the trie */
        remove letter from parent.children
    }
}

searchSecretCodes(board, words) {
    /* Clear any previous answer before starting a fresh search */
    result = empty list

    /* Create the trie root */
    root = new Node()

    /* Insert every word into the trie */
    for each word in words {

        /* Begin insertion from the root */
        node = root

        /* Add all letters of the current word */
        for each ch in word {

            /* Create a child node when this letter is missing */
            if ch not in node.children {

                /* Allocate the new trie node */
                node.children[ch] = new Node()
            }

            /* Move to the child for the next letter */
            node = node.children[ch]
        }

        /* Mark the terminal node with the full word */
        node.word = word
    }

    /* Store the board dimensions for traversal */
    n = size of board
    m = size of board[0]

    /* Try every cell as a starting point */
    for row = 0 to n - 1 {

        /* Scan all columns in the current row */
        for col = 0 to m - 1 {

            /* Start backtracking only if the first letter exists in the trie */
            if root.children contains board[row][col] {

                /* Explore all words that start from this cell */
                backtrack(row, col, root, board)
            }
        }
    }

    if(result is empty){
        return {"[]"}
    }
    /* Return all matched words */
    return result
}
