* **Time Complexity: `O(n^2)`**

  * The outer loop fixes each starting position of a subarray.
  * The inner loop extends that subarray to every possible ending position while updating the product in constant time.
  * The dominant term is `O(n^2)` because every start and end pair is processed once.

