# Single Element II

## Solution 1: Nested Loop Frequency Counting

### Intuition

* The most direct idea is to pick each element and count how many times it appears in the whole array.

* Since every repeated value appears exactly three times, the only value with frequency one is the answer.

* This works for all valid inputs, but it becomes slow because the array is scanned again for every element.

### Approach

* Go through the array one element at a time.

* For each element, scan the full array and count how many times that value appears.

* Return the element whose count is exactly one.

* If no such element is found, return a fallback value.

### Pseudocode

```customtext
singleNumber(arr) {
    /* Store the size of the array */
    n = arr.size()

    /* Check every element in the array */
    for i = 0 to n - 1 {

        /* Count how many times the current element appears */
        count = 0

        for j = 0 to n - 1 {
            if arr[i] == arr[j] {
                count = count + 1
            }
        }

        /* Return the element that appears only once */
        if count == 1 {
            return arr[i]
        }
    }

    /* No single element was found */
    return -1
}
```

