# Fruits & Baskets

## Brute Force Solution

### Intuition

The goal is to find the longest contiguous sequence containing at most `2` distinct fruit types.

* Think of it like sliding a window along the array.

* Expand the window to the right while the number of fruit types in the window is ≤ `2`.

* If a third fruit type appears, shrink the window from the left until there are only `2` types again.

* Keep track of the maximum window size as you slide it represents the maximum fruits you can collect.

### Approach

* Use two nested loops to explore every possible subarray of fruits.

* Keep track of the count of each fruit type in a map.

* Stop expanding the subarray when more than `2` types are included.

* Update the maximum length of valid subarrays and return it.

