# Next Greater Element II

## Solution 1: Circular Nested Scan

### Intuition

* For each element, we can keep moving forward one by one until we either find a bigger value or come back near the same place.
* Since the array is circular, after reaching the end we continue again from the beginning.
* This idea is simple and always works, but it may repeat a lot of comparisons for different positions.

### Approach

* Create an answer array and fill it with minus one because some elements may not have any greater value.
* Check each element one by one as the current element whose answer we want to find.
* From the next position, move forward through at most one full circular pass.
* As soon as a bigger value is found, store it in the answer array and stop searching for that element.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```customtext
nextGreaterElementII(arr) {
    /* Store the size because every search depends on the array length */
    n = arr.size()

    /* Prepare the answer array with -1 so elements with no greater value stay marked */
    ans[n] = {-1}

    /* Check every element as the current starting point */
    for i = 0 to n - 1 {

        /* Move forward through the next n - 1 positions to simulate circular traversal */
        for j = i + 1 to i + n - 1 {

            /* If a greater value appears first in the circular order, record it */
            if arr[j % n] > arr[i] {

                /* Save the first greater value for this position */
                ans[i] = arr[j % n]

                /* Stop because only the first greater value is needed */
                break
            }
        }
    }

    /* Return the completed answer array */
    return ans
}
```

