# Sum of Min Subarray Elements

## Solution 1: Brute Force Approach

### Intuition

* The most direct idea is to generate every contiguous subarray and add its minimum to the answer.
* While extending a subarray from left to right, the minimum can be updated using the previous minimum and the new element, so we do not need to scan the whole subarray again.
* This works for all cases, but it still checks all possible subarrays, so it becomes slow for large arrays.

### Approach

* Pick each position as the starting point of a subarray.
* Extend that subarray one element at a time toward the right.
* Keep track of the smallest value seen so far while extending.
* Add that current smallest value to the final answer for every extension.
* Return the answer after applying modulo `10^8`.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```customtext
sumOfMinSubarrayElements(arr) {
    /* Get the array size so all valid subarray boundaries can be explored */
    n = arr.size()

    /* Store the required modulo value */
    m = 10^8

    /* Start with an empty answer */
    sum = 0

    /* Try every index as the starting point of a subarray */
    for i = 0 to n - 1 {

        /* Reset the running minimum for this new starting point */
        mini = infinity

        /* Extend the subarray step by step toward the right */
        for j = i to n - 1 {

            /* Update the minimum of the current subarray */
            mini = min(mini, arr[j])

            /* Add the current minimum to the final answer */
            sum = (sum + mini) % m
        }
    }

    /* All subarrays have been processed, so return the answer */
    return sum
}
```

