# Binary Tree Paths

## Solution

### Intuition

* Every valid answer must start at the root and end at a leaf, so a path can be built naturally while moving down the tree.
* A depth-first traversal helps us explore one root-to-leaf path completely before trying the next one.
* When we reach a leaf, the current path is one complete answer, and then we remove the last node while returning so the same list can be reused for other paths.

### Approach

* Start a depth-first traversal from the root while keeping a temporary list for the current path.
* Add the current node value to that path whenever a node is visited.
* When a leaf node is reached, store a copy of the current path in the final answer.
* Recursively explore the left and right subtrees.
* Remove the current node from the path after exploring its children so the path stays correct for the next branch.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```plaintext
paths(root, v, ans) {
    /* Stop the traversal when there is no node */
    if root == null {

        /* Nothing to process from an empty node */
        return
    }

    /* Add the current node to the ongoing root-to-current path */
    v.push_back(root->data)

    /* Check whether the current node is a leaf node */
    if root->left == null and root->right == null {

        /* Store this completed root-to-leaf path */
        ans.push_back(v)

        /* Remove the current node before returning to the parent */
        v.pop_back()

        /* This path is finished, so return */
        return
    }

    /* Continue the path through the left subtree */
    paths(root->left, v, ans)

    /* Continue the path through the right subtree */
    paths(root->right, v, ans)

    /* Remove the current node while backtracking */
    v.pop_back()
}

treepaths(root) {
    /* Create the final list that will store all root-to-leaf paths */
    ans = empty 2D list

    /* Return an empty answer when the tree has no nodes */
    if root == null {

        /* No path exists in an empty tree */
        return ans
    }

    /* Create a temporary list to store the current path */
    v = empty list

    /* Start the depth-first traversal from the root */
    paths(root, v, ans)

    /* Return all collected paths */
    return ans
}
```

