# 'O' Within 'X' Boundary

## Solution

### Intuition

* Any group that touches the boundary can never be fully surrounded, so those cells must stay unchanged.
* Instead of checking every group separately, we can start from the boundary and mark all connected safe cells.
* After that, any remaining cell with O must be trapped inside, so we replace it with X.

### Approach

* Create a separate visited grid to mark all safe cells.
* Check every cell on the outer boundary and start a depth-first search from each boundary O.
* During the search, mark every connected O as safe.
* Traverse the inner part of the grid and change every unmarked O into X.

