# Task Completion

## Solution

### Intuition

* The main thing to notice is that this problem becomes impossible only when the prerequisites form a cycle.
* If we keep starting from tasks that currently need no unfinished prerequisite, we can gradually remove valid tasks from the dependency graph.
* If all tasks get processed, completion is possible. If some tasks are still stuck at the end, they must be part of a cycle.

### Approach

* Build a directed graph where each prerequisite points to the task that depends on it.
* Count how many prerequisites each task currently has.
* Put all tasks with no prerequisites into a queue.
* Repeatedly remove one ready task, mark it as completed, and reduce the prerequisite count of tasks unlocked by it.
* At the end, check whether all tasks were processed. If not, a cycle exists, so all tasks cannot be completed.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```plaintext
topologicalSort(adj) {
    /* Store the total number of tasks so all nodes can be checked */
    n = adj.size()

    /* Track how many prerequisites each task still has */
    indegree[n] = {0}

    /* Process tasks with no remaining prerequisites in FIFO order */
    queue q

    /* Store the tasks that can be completed in valid order */
    ans = {}

    /* Count incoming edges for every task */
    for i = 0 to n - 1 {

        /* Visit every task that depends on the current task */
        for each k in adj[i] {

            /* Increase the prerequisite count of that dependent task */
            indegree[k] += 1
        }
    }

    /* Start with tasks that are already ready to be completed */
    for i = 0 to n - 1 {

        /* Only tasks with no prerequisites can enter the queue first */
        if indegree[i] == 0 {

            /* Push the ready task into the queue */
            q.push(i)
        }
    }

    /* Process tasks in topological order */
    while q is not empty {

        /* Take the next available task */
        front = q.front()

        /* Remove it from the queue because it is now being processed */
        q.pop()

        /* Record this task as part of the valid completion order */
        ans.push_back(front)

        /* Visit all tasks unlocked by completing the current task */
        for each k in adj[front] {

            /* One prerequisite of the dependent task is now satisfied */
            indegree[k] -= 1

            /* If the dependent task has no remaining prerequisites, it becomes ready */
            if indegree[k] == 0 {

                /* Push the newly ready task into the queue */
                q.push(k)
            }
        }
    }

    /* If every task was processed, then no cycle exists */
    if ans.size() == n {

        /* Return false because a cycle was not found */
        return false
    }

    /* Some tasks were never processed, so a cycle exists */
    return true
}

taskCompletion(n, P, prerequisites) {
    /* Build an adjacency list for all tasks */
    adj = array of n empty lists

    /* Add each dependency in prerequisite to dependent direction */
    for each i in prerequisites {

        /* Store that task `i.second` must be done before task `i.first` */
        adj[i.second].push_back(i.first)
    }

    /* Return true only when the graph has no cycle */
    return !topologicalSort(adj)
}
